Data Owner - ðŸ‘‰ Accountable for the data; defines classification, access rules, and risk tolerance.
ðŸ“Œ Exam scenario: Decides who may access the data.

Data Custodian -ðŸ‘‰ Implements and maintains controls defined by the data owner (backups, access enforcement).
ðŸ“Œ Exam scenario: Configures permissions and performs backups.

Data Steward -ðŸ‘‰ Ensures data quality, consistency, and compliance with policies and regulations.
ðŸ“Œ Exam scenario: Validates data accuracy and regulatory adherence.

Data Processor -ðŸ‘‰ Processes data on behalf of the data controller under contractual terms.
ðŸ“Œ Exam scenario: Cloud provider handling customer PII.

Data User -ðŸ‘‰ Authorized individual who accesses and uses data according to policy.
ðŸ“Œ Exam scenario: Employee viewing customer records.

Data Subject -ðŸ‘‰ Individual to whom the personal data belongs.
ðŸ“Œ Exam scenario: Customer exercising GDPR rights.

